fields.description: The number of active users in Exchange. Any user who can read and send email is considered an active user.
fields.name: Exchange

fields.description: The number of active users in Microsoft 365. This number includes all the active users in Exchange, OneDrive, SharePoint, Skype For Business, Yammer, and Microsoft Teams. You can find the definition of active user for each product in the respective property description.
fields.name: Office365

fields.description: The number of active users in OneDrive. Any user who viewed or edited files, shared files internally or externally, or synced files is considered an active user.
fields.name: OneDrive

fields.description: The date on which a number of users were active.
fields.name: ReportDate

fields.description: The number of days the report covers.
fields.name: ReportPeriod

fields.description: The latest date of the content.
fields.name: ReportRefreshDate

fields.description: The number of active users in SharePoint. Any user who viewed or edited files, shared files internally or externally, synced files, or viewed SharePoint pages is considered an active user.
fields.name: SharePoint

fields.description: The number of active users in Skype For Business. Any user who organized or participated in conferences, or joined peer-to-peer sessions is considered an active user.
fields.name: SkypeForBusiness

fields.description: The number of active users in Microsoft Teams. Any user who posted messages in team channels, sent messages in private chat sessions, or participated in meetings or calls is considered an active user.
fields.name: Teams

fields.description: The number of active users in Yammer. Any user who can post, read, or like messages is considered an active user.
fields.name: Yammer
